<meta content='Meet the "ems" — machines that emulate human brains and can think, feel and work just like the brains they&#x0027;re copied from. Futurist and social scientist Robin Hanson describes a possible future when ems take over the global economy, running on superfast computers and copying themselves to multitask, leaving humans with only one choice: to retire, forever. Glimpse a strange future as Hanson describes what could happen if robots ruled the earth.' itemprop='description'>
